# Board Banner & Trim

Route: `/tools/board-banner`. Printable cork-board **hardware polish** (header strips + frame trim), not content posters.

## Print model
- Portrait **pack sheets**: letter 8.5×11 (default) or tabloid 11×17
- Multiple short pieces per sheet with **printed** dashed cut marks inside the capture node
- Banner strip heights: 2.5″ / 3.5″ / 4.5″; side/corner edge widths: 1.5″ / 2″ / 2.5″
- Export captures the pack sheet only (PNG + PDF)

## Frame rails (locked)
- **Side** = dual-tone **vertical** rail (primary body + accent stripe) with solid end caps for LOCAL
- **Bottom** = same motif **rotated** — dual-tone horizontal rail with left/right end caps; no chevrons
- **Chevrons are never drawn on side or bottom** — they fought text and mismatched the rail language
- Side columns staple vertically; bottom strips along the frame base
- Corner tiles may still use optional chevron marks with the L-miter

## Shared ornaments (banner + trim)
One Ornaments section applies to both modes:
- Show chevrons (banner / corner only; ignored on side and bottom rails)
- Show local number
- Logo: `none` | `lockup` | `mark` via `BrandLogo variantOverride`
- Show byline + editable byline text (seed from Brand Kit `subText` once; **never** hardcode a union slogan)

## Multi-union
- No union names or slogans in core layout code — Brand Kit / user copy only
- Colours from Brand Kit / ThemePicker; logo from Brand Kit

## Capture-safe colours
Follow `.cursor/rules/comms-module.mdc`: inline hex inside capture nodes; `pickContrastingInk` / `BrandLogo backgroundColor={…}`; keep UI shadows outside `canvasRef`.
